id: pm-6x7o
title: "Relationship governance and completeness audit: semantic edge validation, graph coverage profiles, isolates, stale links, and remediation plans"
description: "Add policy-aware graph quality checks and machine-executable remediation planning without assuming that every root, isolate, or sparse item is defective."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[6]: "area:governance","area:graph",audit,data-quality,relationships,validation
created_at: "2026-07-13T21:59:02.798Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-17T16:10:57.871Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "Audits validate registered kinds, endpoints, direction and inverse rules, payload schema, cardinality, canonical aliases, duplicate identity, provenance, and snapshot consistency; Cycle checks operate only over declared order-bearing kinds and remain separate from associative strongly connected component analysis; Coverage profiles vary by item type, lifecycle state, project profile, age, and role; roots, archives, decisions, reminders, and scratch work can be explicitly valid isolates; Reports include counts, rates, severity, deterministic bounded samples, cursors, change since baseline, and machine-readable issue and remediation codes; Dry-run plans propose exact add, remove, retype, supersede, waive, or investigate operations with confidence and source evidence; no auto-fix invents an edge; Active and terminal remediation are separated; closed-item changes require dedicated changelog-safe batches and immutable audit history; Health, validate, stats, aggregate, and package audit surfaces reuse one SDK policy and finding contract with token-efficient default output"
goal: project management = context management
objective: "Make relationship quality observable, enforceable, explainable, and safely remediable across active and terminal history"
value: Maintainers can distinguish genuine graph debt from intentional sparsity and repair the former without fabricating context
impact: "Prevents dangling, contradictory, cyclic, stale, or meaningless relationship graphs from misleading agents and algorithms"
outcome: "Counts-first audits, bounded samples, profile-aware policies, waivers, dry-run plans, and resumable remediation workflows"
why_now: "Current validation covers basic dependency integrity but the all-status audit exposed isolates, edge-kind drift, shallow ordering chains, and body-to-edge mismatches"
parent: pm-96h7
risk: medium
confidence: high
