comments[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:59:02.798Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: existing validate,deps visualization,and one-time living-map audits do not provide schema-aware graph coverage profiles and remediation plans; this extends canonical governance rather than replacing those items."
  "2026-07-17T13:10:36.159Z",codex-root,"Implementation progress: added a counts-first relationship governance report covering active and terminal dangling references, retired sentinels, ordering-only cycles, stale lifecycle blocks, isolates, sparse nodes, deterministic samples, explicit exemptions, cancellation, and safe remediation text; validation now reuses shared assembly."
  "2026-07-17T13:47:20.393Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: linked governance suite passed; full repository coverage passed 5,798 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; lint/static/security/package gates passed. Fresh packed SDK audit and CLI temp project proved dependency/lifecycle blocked parity, graph assembly, semantic traversal, bounded path evidence, and zero history drift. This tranche is complete; broader type/profile baselines, change-since-baseline, cursors, executable dry-run plans, and all audit-surface integration remain canonical open scope."
  "2026-07-17T14:12:23.856Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 5843a507-bc02-480c-b73f-b95c37e34b46: trimmed/custom governance assemblies now treat missing predecessor detail conservatively as unknown/open instead of falsely reporting a stale lifecycle block. Regression coverage and full exact coverage pass."
  "2026-07-17T15:21:09.861Z",codex-root,"PR #579 review round 1: integrity findings now repartition dangling references with the audit invocation's custom terminal predicate rather than assembly-time defaults. A custom terminal holder regression proves missing_reference_terminal versus missing_reference_active classification. Full 5,800-test coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-17T16:10:55.038Z",codex-sdk-graph,"PR #579 review round 2 evidence: ordering-cycle governance now reports registered allowSelf ordering loops as one-member cycles, and malformed non-string isolate exemptions are ignored safely. Regression proof composes custom registry assembly with self-cycle governance. Full repository coverage passes 298 files / 5,802 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; typecheck, ESLint, zero-clone, 100% docstring, package-boundary, and token-budget gates pass."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T17:08:32.150Z",maintainer-agent,"Manual relationship-density baseline (2026-07-14 pass #82) — the measurement this audit feature should automate. Method: dump .item.dependencies for every ACTIVE item + parent links; degree counts both endpoints; closed-item out-edges not counted (active-graph view). Before enrichment: 211 active items, 269 dep edges + 210 parent edges, 95 items with zero out-edges, 67 items with total degree <= 1 (parent-only). After a 67-edge related-kind enrichment batch: degree<=1 = 3 (pm-7zs0 reminder, pm-x2vx, pm-p5u6 — deliberate; no honest semantic partner). Enrichment structure worth encoding as audit heuristics: (1) scanner-finding clusters get a 2-level hub topology — members -> file-cluster representative -> rule-class representative (Semgrep non-literal-RegExp 30 items across 6 files; prototype-pollution 3; spawn-shell-true 4; dependabot-cooldown 2 under pm-oz8u); (2) story -> implementing-task edges (pm-6ixn -> pm-oz8u); (3) cross-epic complementarity edges documented in bodies but absent as edges (pm-n7rr <-> pm-usfg/pm-pbyu/pm-mpbb); (4) class-sibling edges from defect-family ledgers. Audit check candidates: degree<=1 ratio on active items, container out-degree zero, documented-in-body-but-unlinked pairs."
